## 1. What the Change Should Do

**Goal:** Replace the existing 4-method public API (`load`, `getAllSouls`, `enumerateSouls`, `findMatchingSouls`) on `SoulSpecLoader` with a cleaner 4-method API (`getSoul`, `loadAllSouls`, `listSouls`, `loadSoul`) that fixes three design problems identified by codebase auditing:

| Problem                          | Current behavior                                                                                                                     | New behavior                                                                                   |
| -------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Cache granularity**            | Cache key = `"${userInput}:${level}"` — same soul via "dev" vs "developer" = 2 entries, `souls × levels` blowup                      | Cache key = `path.basename(resolvedDir)` — all inputs for same soul map to one entry           |
| **Loading vs reading conflated** | `load()` does everything (I/O + parse + cache + filter). Repeat calls hit cache but same soul at different levels re-reads from disk | Split: `loadSoul` (I/O + cache write), `getSoul` (cache read + filter). Own concerns separated |
| **console.\* mixed with Effect** | 7 `console.debug`/`console.error` calls inside Effect pipelines (side effects, not typed)                                            | All `Effect.log*` — typed, composable, respects logging config                                 |

