# TP-005-v3: Breaking Refactor — Clean API on `src/loader.ts`

> Version 3 — No backward-compat shims. Breaking refactor. Incorporates Oracle challenge responses, Researcher best-practice fixes, and Scout audit findings.

---

## 1. What the Change Should Do

**Goal:** Replace the entire existing `SoulSpecLoader` public API with a clean 5-method API that separates loading from reading, normalizes cache keys, uses Effect-level logging, and never silently swallows errors. Remove all backward-compatible shims. Rename the service class.

### Why This Is a Breaking Refactor

The `SoulSpecLoader` class is renamed to `SoulLoader`. 4 old methods (`load`, `getAllSouls`, `enumerateSouls`, `findMatchingSouls`) are removed entirely. `EnumeratedSoul` type is no longer exported. All 3 consumer files will fail to compile — this is intentional. The user explicitly requested no backward-compat shims, expecting iterative migration.

### New Public API

| Method                       | Signature                                                   | What it does                                                                                                     |
| ---------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `loadSoul(soulName, level?)` | `Effect<SoulManifest, SoulLoadError, FileSystem \| Path>`   | Resolves path, parses manifest, reads content up to `level` (default 3), caches (upgrade only), returns manifest |
| `loadAllSouls(level?)`       | `Effect<SoulManifest[], SoulLoadError, FileSystem \| Path>` | Crawls `SOUL_SEARCH_PATHS`, calls `loadSoul` each (default level 1). Best-effort per soul.                       |
| `getSoul(soulName, level?)`  | `Effect<SoulManifest, SoulLoadError, FileSystem \| Path>`   | Cache-first, **auto-loads on miss**. Returns level-filtered manifest. Default level = 2.                         |
| `listSouls(level?)`          | `Effect<SoulManifest[], never, never>`                      | Pure cache dump. Level-filtered. Returns `[]` on empty cache — **infallible**.                                   |
| `listSoulNames()`            | `Effect<string[], SoulLoadError, FileSystem \| Path>`       | Scans disk (cache-independent). Lightweight replacement for `getAllSouls()`.                                     |

### Key Design Changes from v2

| v2 decision                                      | v3 fix                                                | Rationale                           |
| ------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| Backward-compat shims                            | Removed entirely                                      | Breaking refactor mandate           |
| `SoulSpecLoader` class                           | Renamed to `SoulLoader`                               | Breaking change makes rename free   |
| `listSouls`: `Effect<..., SoulLoadError, never>` | `Effect<..., never, never>`                           | Infallible — empty = [], not error  |
| `getSoul`: pure cache, fail on miss              | Auto-loads on miss                                    | Eliminates 2-step dance             |
| `getSoul`: `never` requirement                   | `FileSystem \| Path`                                  | Auto-load needs I/O                 |
| Cache: always overwrite                          | Only upgrade, never downgrade                         | Prevents silent cache downgrade bug |
| No `findMatchingSouls` replacement               | Not needed — `listSoulNames()` + consumer-side filter | Keeps API minimal                   |
| `loadAllSouls` per-soul failures: logDebug       | `Effect.logWarning`                                   | Visible by default                  |

---

## 2. New Public API — Detailed Spec

### `loadSoul(soulName, level = 3)`

Always reads from disk. Resolves path → reads `soul.json` → parses → reads content files up to requested level → caches (upgrade only) → returns manifest.

```typescript
const loadSoul = (soulName: string, level: number = 3) => {
  return Effect.gen(function* () {
    const soulPath = yield* resolveSoulPath(soulName);
    const cacheKey = pathSvc.basename(soulPath);
    const manifestPath = `${soulPath}/soul.json`;
    const raw = yield* readJsonFile<Record<string, unknown>>(fs, manifestPath);
    const manifest = parseManifest(raw);
    const files = manifest.files;

    if (level >= 2) {
      if (files.soul) manifest.soul_content = yield* readTextFile(fs, `${soulPath}/${files.soul}`);
      if (files.identity)
        manifest.identity_content = yield* readTextFile(fs, `${soulPath}/${files.identity}`);
    }
    if (level >= 3) {
      if (files.agents)
        manifest.agents_content = yield* readTextFile(fs, `${soulPath}/${files.agents}`);
      if (files.style)
        manifest.style_content = yield* readTextFile(fs, `${soulPath}/${files.style}`);
      if (files.heartbeat)
        manifest.heartbeat_content = yield* readTextFile(fs, `${soulPath}/${files.heartbeat}`);
      if (files.user_template)
        manifest.user_template_content = yield* readTextFile(
          fs,
          `${soulPath}/${files.user_template}`,
        );
      if (manifest.examples?.good)
        manifest.examples_good_content = yield* readTextFile(
          fs,
          `${soulPath}/${manifest.examples.good}`,
        );
      if (manifest.examples?.bad)
        manifest.examples_bad_content = yield* readTextFile(
          fs,
          `${soulPath}/${manifest.examples.bad}`,
        );
    }
    if (files.avatar) {
      const avatarPath = `${soulPath}/${files.avatar}`;
      if (yield* fs.exists(avatarPath)) manifest.avatar_path = avatarPath;
    }

    // Cache: only upgrade, never downgrade
    yield* Ref.update(cache, (m) => {
      const existing = m.get(cacheKey);
      if (existing && existing.cachedLevel >= level) return m;
      return new Map(m).set(cacheKey, { manifest, cachedLevel: level });
    });

    return manifest;
  });
};
```

### `loadAllSouls(level = 1)`

Best-effort crawl. Scans `SOUL_SEARCH_PATHS` → `expandHome` → `readDirectory` → `loadSoul(each)`. Individual failures logged via `Effect.logWarning` and skipped. Fails with `SoulLoadError` if zero souls found.

### `getSoul(soulName, level = 2)`

Cache-first with auto-load. Checks cache → if found and `cachedLevel >= level`, filter and return. Otherwise auto-loads via `loadSoul(soulName, level)`.

**Cache key normalization:** `getSoul` normalizes the lookup key via `resolveSoulPath` + `path.basename` before reading cache, matching how `loadSoul` stores entries. On auto-load fallback, the normalized key is used for cache write.

```typescript
const getSoul = (soulName: string, level: number = 2) => {
  return Effect.gen(function* () {
    // Normalize cache key to match how loadSoul stores entries
    const res = yield* resolveSoulPath(soulName).pipe(
      Effect.catchAll(() => Effect.succeed(null as string | null)),
    );
    const cacheKey = res ? pathSvc.basename(res) : soulName;

    // Cache lookup with normalized key
    const currentCache = yield* Ref.get(cache);
    const entry = currentCache.get(cacheKey);
    if (entry && entry.cachedLevel >= level) {
      return filterByLevel(entry.manifest, level);
    }

    // Auto-load on miss or insufficient level
    return yield* loadSoul(soulName, level).pipe(
      Effect.map((manifest) => filterByLevel(manifest, level)),
      Effect.catchTags({
        SoulNotFoundError: (e) =>
          Effect.fail(new SoulLoadError({ message: `Soul "${soulName}" not found.`, soulName })),
        ManifestParseError: (e) =>
          Effect.fail(
            new SoulLoadError({
              message: `Error parsing soul manifest: ${getErrorMessage(e.cause)}`,
              cause: e.cause,
            }),
          ),
        FileSystemError: (e) =>
          Effect.fail(
            new SoulLoadError({
              message: `File system error: ${getErrorMessage(e.cause)}`,
              cause: e.cause,
            }),
          ),
      }),
      Effect.catchAllCause((cause) => {
        if (Cause.isDieType(cause)) {
          yield *
            Effect.logError(`[loader] Defect loading soul "${soulName}"`, Cause.pretty(cause));
        } else {
          yield *
            Effect.logWarning(
              `[loader] Unexpected error loading soul "${soulName}"`,
              Cause.pretty(cause),
            );
        }
        return Effect.fail(
          new SoulLoadError({ message: "Error loading soul: Unexpected error", cause }),
        );
      }),
    );
  });
};
```

### `listSouls(level = 1)`

Pure cache dump — **infallible**. Empty cache returns `[]`.

```typescript
const listSouls = (level: number = 1) => {
  return Effect.gen(function* () {
    const currentCache = yield* Ref.get(cache);
    return Array.from(currentCache.values()).map((entry) => filterByLevel(entry.manifest, level));
  });
};
```

### `listSoulNames()`

Lightweight disk scan — returns soul directory names without loading content. Replaces `getAllSouls()` for tab-completion and soul-counting.

