## 8. Risks

| Risk                                                      | Impact                                                                                                                                | Mitigation                                                                                                                                         |
| --------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Cache semantics change breaks callers**                 | `load("dev", 1)` then `load("dev", 3)` — second call won't re-load from disk if using `load→loadSoul→filterByLevel`                   | Design: `loadSoul` always reads from disk. Only `getSoul` is pure cache lookup. `load` delegates to `loadSoul` then filters.                       |
| **`enumerateSouls` backward compat**                      | Current `enumerateSouls` loads each soul at level 1 only (fast). If it delegates to `loadAllSouls`, it loads all at level 3 (slower). | Mitigation: `enumerateSouls` shim calls `loadSoul` which loads level 3 (slower but correct). Acceptable perf hit since souls are small text files. |
| **`getAllSouls()` returns cached-only names vs scanning** | Current `getAllSouls()` scans disk every time. If shim delegates to `listSouls()`, it returns only cached souls.                      | Mitigation: Make `getAllSouls()` shim scan disk (not cache). Use `getAllSoulsInternal()` unchanged.                                                |
| **`Effect.log` requires Logger layer**                    | If `Effect.log` logs are silently dropped without a proper logger setup, debugging becomes harder.                                    | Check if current project has a Logger layer. The `logger.ts` file exists. `Effect.logDebug` will work but may need a `LoggerLayer` to see output.  |
| **`filterByLevel` mutates manifest**                      | If we spread and delete instead of deep clone, nested objects (author, compatibility, etc.) are still shared references.              | Acceptable — content fields are top-level optional strings. Delete operations only affect top-level keys. No nested content fields exist.          |
| **TypeScript readonly constraint**                        | `SoulManifest` has `readonly` on all fields. Spreading `{ ...manifest }` loses readonly if we modify.                                 | Use `{ ...manifest, soul_content: undefined }` or a proper filter function that constructs a new object. `delete` on spread loses readonly safety. |

