## 6. Cache Design

### Storage

```typescript
interface CacheEntry {
  readonly manifest: SoulManifest;
  readonly cachedLevel: number;
}

const cache = yield * Ref.make<Map<string, CacheEntry>>(new Map());
```

### Key Derivation

```typescript
// In loadSoul:
const soulPath = yield * resolveSoulPath(soulName);
const pathSvc = yield * Path.Path;
const cacheKey = pathSvc.basename(soulPath);

// In getSoul / listSouls: the caller's soulName IS the cache key
// (since loadSoul normalizes it via basename)
```

### Lifecycle

| Operation                    | Cache read                      | Cache write                                     |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| `loadSoul("dev", 2)`         | No                              | Yes — key `"developer"`, level 2 manifest       |
| `loadSoul("dev", 3)`         | No                              | Yes — overwrites key `"developer"` with level 3 |
| `getSoul("developer", 2)`    | Yes — finds `"developer"`       | No                                              |
| `getSoul("developer", 3)`    | Yes — checks `cachedLevel >= 3` | No                                              |
| `listSouls(1)`               | Yes — iterates all entries      | No                                              |
| `loadAllSouls(1)`            | No                              | Yes — one entry per discovered soul             |
| `enumerateSouls()`           | No (delegates to loadAllSouls)  | Yes (via loadAllSouls)                          |
| `load("dev", 2)` — fast path | Yes — checks `getSoul` first    | No (if cached)                                  |
| `load("dev", 2)` — slow path | No                              | Yes (delegates to loadSoul)                     |

### Cache Upgrade

A soul cached at level 1 can be "upgraded" by calling `loadSoul("dev", 3)` — it overwrites the cache entry with a level-3 manifest. This is how a `/soul developer` command after `list_souls` works efficiently: `list_souls` loads everything at level 1 (fast), then `/soul developer` triggers `load("developer", 2)` which checks cache → finds `"developer"` at level 1 → cache miss for level 2 → calls `loadSoul("developer", 3)` → re-reads from disk → cache now has level 3.

