## 4. Cache Design

### Storage

```typescript
interface CacheEntry {
  readonly manifest: SoulManifest;
  readonly cachedLevel: number;
}

const cache = yield * Ref.make<Map<string, CacheEntry>>(new Map());
```

### Key Derivation

```typescript
const soulPath = yield * resolveSoulPath(soulName);
const pathSvc = yield * Path.Path;
const cacheKey = pathSvc.basename(soulPath); // normalizes "dev" → "developer"
```

| Input to `loadSoul`           | Resolved path                 | Cache key     |
| ----------------------------- | ----------------------------- | ------------- |
| `"developer"`                 | `~/.pi/agent/souls/developer` | `"developer"` |
| `"dev"` (partial match)       | `~/.pi/agent/souls/developer` | `"developer"` |
| `"/home/user/custom/my-soul"` | `/home/user/custom/my-soul`   | `"my-soul"`   |

### Upgrade-Only Policy

`loadSoul` only updates cache if `newLevel > cachedLevel`. Calling `loadSoul("dev", 1)` after `loadSoul("dev", 3)` returns a level-1 manifest but the cache stays at level 3. `getSoul("dev", 3)` still works after a downgrade attempt.

### Cache Lifecycle

| Operation                  | Cache read               | Cache write                       |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------ | --------------------------------- |
| `loadSoul("dev", 2)`       | No                       | Yes — key `"developer"`, level 2  |
| `loadSoul("dev", 3)`       | No                       | Yes — overwrites key with level 3 |
| `getSoul("dev", 2)` — hit  | Yes — cache hit          | No                                |
| `getSoul("dev", 3)` — miss | Yes — insufficient level | Auto-load via loadSoul            |
| `listSouls(1)`             | Yes — iterates all       | No                                |
| `loadAllSouls(1)`          | No                       | Yes — one per discovered soul     |

