Remove the `Effect.catchAll(() => Effect.succeed(null))` anti-pattern from all success-path tests in `tests/services/loader.test.ts`. The `catchAll(null)` pattern silently converts typed Effect failures into opaque `null` values, losing error diagnostics, type information, and interrupt detection. `it.effect` (from `@effect/vitest`) already has built-in error handling — it captures the `Exit` via `Effect.exit`, calls `Cause.prettyErrors()`, and throws the first error as a plain JS Error that Vitest formats with full stack traces. Removing the `catchAll` wrappers is purely a diagnostic improvement: tests that failed before (via `expect(null).not.toBeNull()`) will now fail with the actual `SoulLoadError` message. No production source files are touched.

