## 5. Risks and Mitigations

| #     | Risk                                                                                                                                                                               | Likelihood                             | Impact                                      | Mitigation                                                                                                                                  |
| ----- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **1** | **Test ordering dependency (pre-existing)** — `SoulSpecLoader.Default` is a singleton. Test 3 (`listSouls returns []`) sees cache entries from earlier tests if run order changes. | Medium — parallelization triggers this | High — silent false negative                | **Document only.** Not caused by this change. Currently passes because tests run in source order. Do not reorder tests without fixing this. |
| **2** | **CI environment lacks soul fixtures**                                                                                                                                             | High — no test fixtures exist          | Medium — tests fail with `SoulLoadError`    | Expected. The error message is now diagnostic-quality instead of `0 > 0`. Pre-existing problem.                                             |
| **3** | **Test 5 zero-soul edge case** — `loadAllSouls` fails on zero souls by design                                                                                                      | High (no souls = same as risk #2)      | Low — diagnostic improvement                | Both before and after: test fails. Before: `expected 0 to be greater than 0`. After: `SoulLoadError: No souls found in any search path.`    |
| **4** | **Developer conflates test anti-pattern with production catchAll**                                                                                                                 | Low (scope is explicit)                | Medium — could break best-effort collection | **Out-of-scope declaration in §6** is explicit. Brief rationale for each production usage.                                                  |

### Safety confirmation: production catchAll does not mask test errors

The production code `getSoul` has its own `catchAll` on `resolveSoulPath` (loader.ts:348). Removing test-level `catchAll` does **not** change behavior — `getSoul` will succeed (with a cached entry or via `loadSoul`) or `loadSoul` will fail with `SoulLoadError`. The test sees the exact same behavior, just with better error messages. **Safe to remove.**

