### The Double-Catch Problem (Sites 2 and 4)

The pattern `Effect.catchTags(...)` → `Effect.catchAllCause(...)` has a fundamental flaw when `catchTags` handlers **re-fail** (produce `Effect.fail(new Error(...))`):

```
Body fails with SomeError
  → catchTags catches it, produces Effect.fail(new SoulLoadError("specific message"))
    → catchAllCause catches this SoulLoadError (it's a Fail leaf in the Cause)
      → logs "Unexpected error" and re-fails with SoulLoadError("generic message")
        → SPECIFIC MESSAGE LOST
```

Both `catchAllCause` and `catchAll` have this problem. The only safe post-`catchTags` combinator when handlers re-fail is `catchAllDefect`, which only catches `Die` leaves.

### `Cause.isDieType` vs `Cause.isDie`

Both Sites 2 and 4 use `Cause.isDieType(cause)` which matches only a `Die` singleton leaf. If a cause is `Sequential` (e.g., from `Effect.ensuring` where both sections fail) or `Parallel` (concurrent failures) containing a `Die`, `Cause.isDieType` returns `false`. The recursive `Cause.isDie(cause)` checks all branches of the cause tree. The recommended fix (switch to `catchAllDefect`) makes this distinction moot — `catchAllDefect` handles `Die` leaves correctly regardless of composition.

[Source: Cause guards — `isDieType` vs `isDie`](https://effect.website/docs/data-types/cause/#guards)

### Platform Error Handling Gap

The `loadSoul` body calls `@effect/platform` `fs.exists`, `fs.readDirectory`, etc. directly. These can fail with `PlatformError` (`_tag: "SystemError"`). The current `catchTags` maps `"FileSystemError"` (the custom error from `readJsonFile`/`readTextFile`) but NOT `"SystemError"` (the platform error). With the recommended fix of removing `catchAllCause`/`catchAll`, these platform errors would escape to the caller.

Two remediation approaches:

1. **(Recommended)** Map platform errors inside the `Effect.gen` body using `Effect.mapError` to convert them to `FileSystemError` — already done in `readJsonFile` and `readTextFile`. Extend to `fs.exists` and `fs.readDirectory` calls.
2. Add `Effect.catchTag("SystemError", ...)` after `catchTags` — quick but fragile if platform adds new error tags.

