| 5   | Log messages consistent?       | ✅ Yes                 | Specific labels, consistent `[loader]` prefix, defensive `getErrorMessage()`.                              |
| 6   | Over-abstraction?              | ❌ No                  | Helper is minimal. Team correctly chose not to abstract SystemError/BadArgument handlers further.          |
| 7   | More maintainable?             | ✅ Yes, partially      | High-severity issues fixed. Medium-severity DRY items (dir scanning, catchAllDefect duplication) deferred. |

**Net assessment:** The changes improve maintainability by eliminating two double-wrap bugs, making error handling type-safe and explicit, and centralizing `SoulLoadError` construction. The only regression is the flatMap zero-results check (stylistic, not blocking). Four scout findings remain unaddressed, but these were correctly scoped as deferred work.

