**2. `loadSoul` always-disk on repeat calls** (Medium) — The backward-compat `load` shim delegates to `loadSoul` which re-reads everything from disk every time. Current code checks cache first (near-free on repeat). Every `/soul developer` command re-reads all 9 files. A shim that checks `getSoul` cache before falling back to `loadSoul` would fix this.

**3. Cache key collision** — Two souls with the same name in different search paths: first-found-wins silently. Already current behavior, but the plan inherits and doesn't document it.

